{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix deprecated ASN.1 decoder API usage in F1AP positioning functions\n\n### Summary\nThe F1AP positioning functionality was using deprecated `aper_decode()` API calls which have known safety and correctness issues. Additionally, the file `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.c` referenced in static analysis was missing from the codebase.\n\nThe deprecated API usage could lead to buffer overflows or incorrect decoding under certain network conditions when processing positioning measurement requests from gNB-DU to gNB-CU.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_handlers.c`: Updated main F1AP PDU decoder to use `aper_decode_complete()` instead of deprecated `aper_decode()`\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.c`: Created new file with positioning measurement functions using modern ASN.1 API\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_positioning.h`: Created new header file for positioning functionality\n- `openair2/F1AP/f1ap_common.h`: Added include for positioning header\n\n"
}